# Manylogue configuration — all optional. Copy to <home>/.manylogue/.env (secrets belong
# there) or to a ./.env in the directory you launch from (dev fallback; can set
# MANYLOGUE_HOME). Precedence: process env > <home>/.manylogue/.env > ./.env.

# Where Manylogue keeps its config (agents, roles) and chat history.
# Defaults to ~/.manylogue. Point it at a repo checkout during development if you prefer.
# MANYLOGUE_HOME=/path/to/manylogue-home

# Log verbosity: DEBUG, INFO, WARNING, ERROR. Defaults to DEBUG.
# MANYLOGUE_LOG_LEVEL=INFO
